fn.p:
aFractional inhibitory concentration index (FICI) was calculated with the following formula: 

 \documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{upgreek} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} }{}$\sum FIC\ = \ FICA + FICB\ = \ ( {\frac{{C_A^{combi}}}{{MIC_A^{alone}}}} ) + \frac{{C_B^{combi}}}{{MIC_B^{alone}}}\ $\end{document}
, where 

 \documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{upgreek} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} }{}$C_A^{combi}$\end{document}
 and 

 \documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{upgreek} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} }{}$C_B^{combi}$\end{document}
 are the inhibitory concentrations of the drugs A and B in the combinations and 

 \documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{upgreek} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} }{}$MIC_A^{alone}$\end{document}
 and 

 \documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{upgreek} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document} }{}$MIC_B^{alone}$\end{document}
 are the inhibitory concentrations of drugs A and B when acting individually. A FICI ≤0.5 is considered synergistic (S), a FICI >0.5–≤4 is indifferent (I) and a FICI >4 is antagonistic (A).
